page.title: 17HOUSING
page.content: When we look out of our windows at John Selden First School, we see three different types of private housing. On two sides of the school field semi-detached bungalows can be found. On the Nelson Road side, where the school entrance is, the housing is made up of semi-detached and detached houses. Most of the area has been built up within the last 20 years. To the south of the school in the Maybridge Estate, where many of our school children live is council housing. The houses are mostly semi-detached but there are some terraced town houses.A few purpose built flats can be seen in Goring Street at the west end of the estate. North of the school all the houses are privately owned. Most of them are bungalows.
